### User Management Service — REST Client requests (VS Code "REST Client" extension)
### Variables below; override @baseUrl etc. per environment. Chained values
### (userId, jwt) are captured from responses automatically by REST Client
### when you click "Send Request" in order, top to bottom.

@baseUrl = http://localhost:3000
@adminBearerToken = your_admin_bearer_token_here
@username = httpuser{{$timestamp}}
@email = httpuser{{$timestamp}}@example.com
@password = Sup3r$ecretPW1
@newPassword = N3wSup3r$ecretPW2

### 1. Health check
GET {{baseUrl}}/health

### 2. Register user
# @name register
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/users/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "username": "{{username}}",
  "emailAddress": "{{email}}",
  "password": "{{password}}",
  "passwordConfirmation": "{{password}}"
}

### 3. Activate user
### Set activationToken manually — from the activation email, or in local dev:
### SELECT token_value FROM activation_tokens WHERE user_id = '{{register.response.body.userId}}';
@activationToken = REPLACE_ME
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/users/activate
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "token": "{{activationToken}}"
}

### 4. Admin: resend confirmation email
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/admin/users/{{register.response.body.userId}}/resend-confirmation
Authorization: Bearer {{adminBearerToken}}

### 5. Send OTP
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/otp/send
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "userId": "{{register.response.body.userId}}"
}

### 6. Resend OTP
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/otp/resend
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "userId": "{{register.response.body.userId}}"
}

### 7. Login
# @name login
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "{{email}}",
  "password": "{{password}}"
}

### 8. Call an authenticated endpoint (request account deletion, proves session middleware works)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/users/deletion-requests
Authorization: Bearer {{login.response.body.token}}

### 9. Cancel that deletion request (keep the account alive for the rest of the flow)
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/users/deletion-requests
Authorization: Bearer {{login.response.body.token}}

### 10. Logout
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/auth/logout
Authorization: Bearer {{login.response.body.token}}

### 11. Password recovery request
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/auth/password-recovery
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "{{email}}"
}

### 12. Password reset
### Set recoveryToken manually — from the recovery email, or in local dev:
### SELECT token FROM password_recovery_requests WHERE user_id = '{{register.response.body.userId}}' ORDER BY requested_at DESC LIMIT 1;
@recoveryToken = REPLACE_ME
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/auth/password-reset
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "recovery_token": "{{recoveryToken}}",
  "new_password": "{{newPassword}}"
}

### 13. Login again with the new password
# @name loginAgain
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "{{email}}",
  "password": "{{newPassword}}"
}

### 14. Request account deletion (for real this time)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/users/deletion-requests
Authorization: Bearer {{loginAgain.response.body.token}}

### 15. Confirm account deletion
### Set deletionToken manually — from the deletion-confirmation email, or in local dev:
### SELECT token_value FROM account_deletion_requests WHERE user_id = '{{register.response.body.userId}}' AND status = 'pending';
@deletionToken = REPLACE_ME
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/users/deletion-requests/confirm
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "token": "{{deletionToken}}"
}

### 16. Attempt login — must fail (401) since the account is deleted
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "{{email}}",
  "password": "{{newPassword}}"
}
